&lt;p&gt;BioMed Realty is seeking an AI Solutions Lead to serve as the organization’s dedicated resource for the evaluation, deployment, and ongoing oversight of artificial intelligence tools across all business functions. This is a cross-functional, individual contributor role that bridges technology and operations, translating AI capability into practical, compliant, and measurable business value. The AI Solutions Lead will be responsible for monitoring the effectiveness of all currently deployed AI, researching and vetting emerging tools, collaborating with each department to design and deliver user training, and working alongside Legal and Compliance to ensure that the organization’s AI use meets applicable regulatory and contractual standards.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role is pivotal as BioMed accelerates its AI adoption across Property Management &amp;amp; Operations, Accounting, Asset Management, Legal, Construction, and corporate functions. The ideal candidate is intellectually curious, operationally minded, and able to communicate equally well with property managers, accountants, engineers, and senior leadership.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role is a key contributor to how senior management, the Board, and investors understand portfolio performance. The Analyst / Senior Analyst will transform leasing, occupancy, and development data into actionable analysis and reporting that supports executive decision-making.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;AI Portfolio Monitoring and Performance Management&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain a current inventory of all AI tools and agentic workflows deployed across the organization, including vendor, use case, data inputs, business owner, and deployment date.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define and track key performance indicators for each deployed AI tool, time saved, error rate, adoption rate, cost per transaction and report findings to CTO on a regular cadence.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor AI outputs on an ongoing basis to detect performance degradation, model drift, hallucinations, or systematic errors; escalate material issues and coordinate remediation with vendors and affected departments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct periodic reviews of deployed tools against evolving alternatives, recommending upgrades, replacements, or discontinuation as appropriate.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain documentation of prompts, configurations, exceptions, and change history for all deployed AI tools to support audit and compliance review.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Research, Evaluation, and Vendor Management&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Continuously monitor the AI tool landscape, including CRE-specific platforms, horizontal agentic frameworks, and ERP-embedded AI capabilities to identify emerging solutions relevant to BioMed’s operations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and apply a standardized evaluation framework for new AI tools, assessing capability, data security posture, integration readiness, vendor stability, pricing, and contractual risk.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead proof-of-concept and pilot engagements, defining success criteria, managing timelines, coordinating participating departments, and producing go/no-go recommendations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and maintain relationships with AI vendors, attend industry conferences and demonstrations, and serve as the organization’s primary point of contact for inbound vendor inquiries related to AI.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prepare concise evaluation summaries and business cases for leadership review, clearly articulating expected ROI, implementation effort, and risk.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Departmental Collaboration and Workflow Design&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with department heads and functional leads across Accounting, Property Management &amp;amp; Operations, Asset Management, Legal,

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;BioMed Realty&lt;/strong&gt;, a Blackstone portfolio company, is the largest private provider of real estate solutions for the life science industry. BioMed owns and operates high-quality life science real estate in leading innovation markets across the United States and the United Kingdom, including Boston/Cambridge, San Francisco, San Diego, Seattle, Boulder, and Cambridge, U.K.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Opportunity&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role is a key contributor to how senior management, the Board, and investors understand portfolio performance. The Analyst / Senior Analyst will transform leasing, occupancy, and development data into actionable analysis and reporting that supports executive decision-making.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This position offers a strong opportunity for a finance professional who enjoys working at the intersection of data, reporting, and business insight. The role includes ownership of recurring executive and investor deliverables, ad hoc portfolio analysis, and collaboration with teams across the company to help explain what is happening in the business. It is well suited for someone who is highly analytical, detail-oriented, and comfortable operating in a fast-paced environment with multiple priorities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Title and level will be determined based on experience, skill set, and demonstrated ability in financial reporting, analysis, and cross-functional partnership.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prepare recurring dashboards and reporting packages for senior management and investors, including portfolio occupancy reporting, quarterly investor presentations, and responses to ad hoc investor requests&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Analyze portfolio performance trends, including occupancy, leasing activity, tenant mix, and development activity, and translate findings into clear reporting and presentations for senior management and investors&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide concise analysis, summaries, and supporting materials to help leadership understand portfolio performance and key business trends at both the asset and portfolio levels&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead the monthly rent roll variance review process to ensure data accuracy in executive and investor reporting, partnering with Lease Administration to investigate and resolve discrepancies&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Review and analyze lease transactions and related documentation to support portfolio metrics and reporting accuracy&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage leasing and portfolio databases, ensuring data quality, consistency, and reliability across reporting deliverables&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with teams across the company to coordinate data flow and support accurate, timely, and consistent reporting&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform detailed reviews of reporting materials to ensure accuracy, grammar, formatting, and consistency across deliverables&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Utilize Excel, PowerPoint, and the organization’s enterprise reporting software, Oracle EPM Cloud, to support analysis and reporting responsibilities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify opportunities to improve reporting processes, data quality, and the efficiency of recurring deliverables&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What Success Looks Like in This Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will likely thrive in this role if you:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Are energized by a fast-paced environment and enjoy managing multiple concurrent deadlines&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Take pride in producing thoughtful, polished, high-quality work with a high degree of accuracy&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Can move effectively between recurring production work and ad hoc analysis without losing momentum&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Enjoy working with large data sets and translating them into clear, useful insights.&lt;/li&gt;
